places.address: Masjidur Rahman TNTJ, 12/1, Pallivasal street, Kochi - Dhanushkodi route, Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu 623526

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is a beautiful Masjid ironically situated at a corner of the APJ Abdul Kalam's house in Rameswaram.

The thousands of people thronging to this monument can pray the five times prayers if and when they are Muslims.

The place has been categorically upscale by now, and the APJ Abdul Kalam International Foundation adds up to this International yet too simple landmark.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Alhamdulillah very beautiful masjid with all the required facilities. This masjid is in close vicinity to Dr APJ Abdul Kalam's house and also Railway Station.
Kalam sir was also a musalli of this masjid.

featured_reviews.review_id: Spacious mosque near rameshwaram railway station. Calm and cool place in the middle of residential area. House of late former president Abdul Kalam is meters away. It's interesting that you can see century old tradition of beating drum before azan here.
